Imagineshining a flashlight from your point. Ifthe light crosses a polygon's edges anodd number of times, you're inside. Evenyou're outside. It's like a game of tagwith shapes. But here's the catch. Whatif you're on the edge? The code saysnope. Stick to the rules. It also checksif the polygon is valid. Nowwe can relate T of S to V out of S whereV out of S is T of S * G of S. Weeventually want to find the transferfunction V out over V in. title: How Inductors Work (Basic Principles) ⚙️ #electronics  #inductor #components #circuit
subtitle: This tiny electronic component in yourdevice ensures a smooth flow of current.An inductor is a small device that stores energyand helps regulate current during fluctuations.Inductors vary in size and shape,but fundamentally, they consist of a wire coilelegantly wound around a ferromagnetic core.It follows Faraday's and Lenz's laws, henceresisting any changes in current. When currentincreases, it counters with opposing force;when it decreases, it resists by pushingelectrons out to maintain stability.It's symbolised in the circuit with thissymbol, similar to resistance, right?In this parallel circuit setup, the inductorinitially resists current changes. Over time,it acts as an open circuit, allowing current flow.When the power supply is off, the inductor powersthe load briefly until energy is depleted.Inductors are very crucial component inelectronics, To understand their functionin detail, please watch the full video

subtitle: Will Desmos save you on the SAT? Kindof, but only if you use it right. See,most students either never touch Desmosor rely on it way too much. The realsecret, knowing when to use it. Here arethe two ways smart test takers useDesmos. One, to solve specific questiontypes faster. For example, if you useDesmos for questions like these, you'llspeed through the exam. System ofequations, quadratics, linearregressions, trig functions, andinequalities. But it doesn't just endwith solving questions. Another way topscorers leverage Desmos is to doublechcheckck their work. Many times it makesmore sense to solve a question by handthan verify it with Desmos in 5 seconds.This catches those tiny calculationerrors that cost pickpoints. Want moreSAT hacks? subtitle: If you place two pins on a surface andtie a thread between them and draw a line like this,you will get an amazing geometric shapewhich is called ellipse.  These two pinholes are called focus points.  The special thing isthat if you draw a line from any focus point,it willalways reach the second focus point after hitting the wall.And if a table of the same shape is made, then you canclose your eyes and throw the ball in any direction.It will go into the hole on its own.And the most interesting thing is that if you stand atone focus point in a large elf shaped room,you canclearly hear even the whisper of a person standing at the other focus point.Even if it is 100 feet away from you.One such authentic room is at St.Paul's in Minnesotacalled the Whispering Gallery.  Hmm

Only then do theparts of the brain develop more,and that's what increases your thinking skills.

id: 💥Can Non-Math Students Do BBA？ 😱Maths Required for BBA？ #Shorts #BBA #BBACourse #BBAAdmissions [KYXNxEQWBEM]
video: ./part_1/digital_humanities_m/💥Can Non-Math Students Do BBA？ 😱Maths Required for BBA？ #Shorts #BBA #BBACourse #BBAAdmissions [KYXNxEQWBEM].mp4
title: 💥Can Non-Math Students Do BBA? 😱Maths Required for BBA? #Shorts #BBA #BBACourse #BBAAdmissions
subtitle: Is math necessary to pursue a BBA course?Let's find out. There aremany benefits of taking math as a subject in 12th grade,but youcan pursue a BBA course without math. In the BBA syllabus,you'll find some math conceptsthat are at the 10th-grade level, but with theright approach and strategy, youcan tackle math as a subject. In BBA,you'll study business mathematics,which isn't very advanced; it's at a verybasic level, whicheven an average student can clear. title: Exponential growth v/s Logistic growth #neet #class12 #biology #study #shorts #shortsvideo #board
subtitle: Let's quickly differentiate between exponential growth andlogistic growth kids. Exponentialgrowth represents such population growthwhere there are unlimited resources, then thesize of the population keeps on increasing with time,but logistic growthrepresents population growth with limited resources.In exponential growth, unlimited resources are being talked about, whereasin logistic growth, limitedresources are being talked about.Exponential growth is less realistic. It is notpossible to have unlimited resources in the environment, that iswhy logistic growth is more realistic as comparedto exponential growth. In the exponentialgrowth model, aJ-shaped curve is obtained, where asin the case of logistic growth model, a sigma-likecurve is obtained. Exponential growth doesnot talk about any upper limit, it saysunlimited resources, unlimited populationgrowth, but logistic growth talks about an upper limitwhich is called carryingcapacity. Carrying capacity is that noWhat is the maximum number ofindividuals a habitat can support? If ahabitat's population exceeds its carrying capacity, thepopulation growthrate will begin to decline.

Exponentialgrowth represents such population growthwhere there are unlimited resources, then thesize of the population keeps on increasing with time,but logistic growthrepresents population growth with limited resources.In exponential growth, unlimited resources are being talked about, whereasin logistic growth, limitedresources are being talked about.Exponential growth is less realistic. It is notpossible to have unlimited resources in the environment, that iswhy logistic growth is more realistic as comparedto exponential growth. In the exponentialgrowth model, aJ-shaped curve is obtained, where asin the case of logistic growth model, a sigma-likecurve is obtained. Exponential growth doesnot talk about any upper limit, it saysunlimited resources, unlimited populationgrowth, but logistic growth talks about an upper limitwhich is called carryingcapacity. Carrying capacity is that noWhat is the maximum number ofindividuals a habitat can support? If ahabitat's population exceeds its carrying capacity, thepopulation growthrate will begin to decline.

id: AI and Machine Learning in Computational Physics [B5hcndtjGds]
video: ./part_1/computational_physic/AI and Machine Learning in Computational Physics [B5hcndtjGds].mp4
title: AI and Machine Learning in Computational Physics
subtitle: [Music]Computational physics uses numericalmethods to simulate physical systems. AIand machine learning enhancecomputational physics, enabling fastersolutions. AI integration leads to moreaccurate solutions for complex physicalproblems. Machine learning models canapproximate solutions to partialdifferential equations. Neural networksand reinforcement learning algorithmsare examples of machine learning modelsused for approximation. These modelsidentify patterns in large data sets andaid in discovering new physical lawsfrom experimental data. The field of AIin computational physics faceschallenges including modelinterpretability. Data scarcity presentsa significant obstacle to the effectiveapplication of AI and physics. Ensuringphysical consistency in AI predictionsis crucial for reliable simulations.

id: AI's Math Mystery Solved (3 Visual Hacks That Boost Performance 2%) #Shorts [-jMqR99G3YU]
video: ./part_1/computer_vision_math/AI's Math Mystery Solved (3 Visual Hacks That Boost Performance 2%) #Shorts [-jMqR99G3YU].mp4
title: AI's Math Mystery Solved (3 Visual Hacks That Boost Performance 2%) #Shorts
subtitle: Ever wonder why AI stumbles over mathdiagrams? A breakthrough study shows theanswer lies in how images are presented?Researchers tested QN2 5-7B. It solved28.5% of problems with captions, butonly 25.4% with actual images. Why?Models can describe visuals, butstruggle to reason with them, like atour guide who can't solve a puzzle froma layout. The fix: simple visual tricks.One, distractor concatenation, pairingmath with random images. Two, dominancepreserving mixup, blending visuals whilekeeping key details. Three, randomrotation, testing geometry understandingregardless of orientation. These tweaksboosted math performance by 2%, provingthat better visual training equalssmarter AI. The future isn't just aboutsolving problems, it's about seeing themclearly. Stay curious.

subtitle: Ever wondered how AI turns a woodenchair into a metal one or swapsbackgrounds without glitches? Let'sbreak down the math behind modern imageediting. Researchers developed Freine, aframework that blends three smarttechniques. Temporally contextualattention, tracks changes over time,local perturbation, fine-tunes details,and content specified generation.Focuses on specific areas. This lets AIdo everything from swapping textures tocomposing cross image scenes withprecision. For example, appearancetransfer keeps an object's shape butchanges its look, like making a treeglow. Cross image composition movesobjects between photos seamlessly. Whilepartial mask editing lets you tweak tinyregions without affecting the wholeimage. Tested on GeoBench, a data setwith 6,000 editing tasks, Freefineoutperforms older methods by reducingartifacts and improving consistency.It's not perfect. Extreme changes stillchallenge the model, but it's a giantleap for tools in photo editing, VR, andbeyond. Next time you see a flawless AIedit, remember it's math, creativity,and a dash of smart code. Stay curious.

title: Ecological Pyramid | Types of Ecological Pyramids #class12 #neet #shorts #biology #shortsvideo
subtitle: Children, what does a pyramid look like? Anecological pyramid is a graphicalrepresentation between different livingorganisms at different trophic levels.Children, in an ecological pyramid, the baserepresents theproducers. Above that comes yoursecond trophic level, that is, primaryconsumers. Then above that, secondaryconsumers. Then above that, tertiary consumers. There arethree types of ecological pyramids:Pyramid of number, Pyramid of biomass,Pyramid of energy. Pyramid of energy isupright for every ecosystem. The base containsmore energy. As wemove upwards, the energy decreases.Why is this so? Children, because you allknow that the law of 10 states that as wemove from one tropic level to the higher nexttropic level, only energyis transferred at 10. That is why an upright pyramid isformed. In most ecosystems, thepyramid of number, biomass, energy isupright. However, someecosystems show exceptions andinverted pyramids. We willknow what those exceptions are in the next shorts.Stay tuned.  Biology 8th

An examplewould be the matrix 3113* the vector 1 1 equaling 4 * the vector1 1. A matrix can only have as many igenvalues/igenvectors as its size. video: ./part_1/cosmology_mathematic/How can you turn an object into a Black hole？ #shorts #space #science #astronomy [80Bxb8eoLtM].mp4
title: How can you turn an object into a Black hole? #shorts #space #science #astronomy
subtitle: As I told you earlier,any object, even you,can turn into a black hole ifsqueezed to a certain extent. Buthow does an object actually become a black hole?Look, all matter has gravity, andgravity depends on the mass of the object and its distance. Thefarther away the matter is, the weaker its gravity.For example, when youstand on a plant, your bodyfeels the gravity of all the atoms of that plant,even thefarthest atom of that planet.Because of this, you are standing properly on that plant. The same thing happenswith the Earth and its gravity. But if yousqueeze that plant and make it smaller, all theatoms will come very close to each other, due to whichyou will be able to feel the gravity of that planet evenmore. And if you keepsqueezing that planet even more, then ata certain point, that planet will become sosmall that even lightcannot reflect from it.  And thus thatplanet will convert into a black hole.

subtitle: If we cross the event horizon of a black hole, is itpossible to escape from there?Sitting in the fastest rocket till date, we aretrying to escape from the event horizon,but you will realize in a short whilethat this much speed is not enough to escape from therebecause toescape from the event horizon, your escape velocity should bemore than the speed of light andif this does not happen then you will fall back into the black hole. So,can we escape from there with the help of a chain or rope? It would befoolish to say so.Only one idea comes in front of usand that is teleportation with the help of which youcan easily get out of the black hole,but as you must be knowing that the idea of ​​teleportis a myth, regarding which we donot have any proper evidence.

subtitle: You know about the most unique coincidence in our solar system?When welook at the sun and moon in the sky,they appear the same size. This isbecause the sun is exactly 400 times wider than the moonand is also 150 million kilometers away from us.Whereas the moon is exactly 400times closer to the Earth, due to which the sun andmoon appear the same size to us. Andbecause of these things, solar eclipses are also possible.Well, most people know this much,but did you know that out of the293 moons in the solar system, ourmoon is the only one due to which a solareclipse is possible?
